rates them with contemporary examples. Designed to introduce a wide readership to international development, the book: • considers how far the field has been reconfigured over time and to what extent it is likely to change in the future; • reviews contemporary topics including tourism, migration and digital technologies; • includes distinctive international case studies and examples. By providing a succinct evaluation of competing approaches to, and perspectives on, the idea and practice of international development, this book offers students across the social sciences a distinct and invaluable introduction to the field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBusiness. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Sustainable Development.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831111967700 cprintz978144734882540uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447348856?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447348856423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447348856/original  a978-3-11-119677-0  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles